[SN]TITLE[SN]
Londonderry: Man charged over serious assault in Waterloo Street

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 22-year-old man has been charged by police over an assault in Londonderry which left a man critically injured.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The injured man, who is also in his 20s, was attacked in Waterloo Street at 00:45 BST on Sunday.
The 22-year-old man was arrested a short time later.  Detectives have now charged him with causing grievous bodily harm (GBH) with intent.
He has also been charged with possession of a Class A drug and is due in court in Derry on Monday.
